   This lawsuit is quite frankly, BS.  I invite Mr. Novak to try to sue me, I really do.  You cannot be found guilty of slander, or libel in this case, if what you speak is TRUE.  Truth is a defense; I learned that years ago in my Ethics classes.  Sure there are exceptions to this, but from what I read in that article none of them apply.  <br>
<br>
 Idiots like Novak make me ill. <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171494</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uverylowsodium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VERY LOW SODIUM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/18/02 1:30:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27165.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> In some countries, bulletin boards are considered publications, and BBs and users posting there can be held accountable for any post.<br>
<br>
However:<br>
&quot;While not every message posted in a public forum is safe, a CA court's decision seems to convey that unless the message is framed as a form of fact, then any message posted to a public internet forum should be considered as opinion, and thus cannot be considered as a libelous comment.&quot;<br>
